05522nam a22008535i 9783110922172DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20121999gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109221727 a10.1515/97831109221722doi  a(DE-B1597)46916  a(OCoLC)979735617  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 7aLIT0000002bisacsh  aMH 842702rvk0(DE-625)rvk/122919:1207200aPolitik und Religion im Judentum /chrsg. von Christoph Miething. 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2012] 4c©1999  a1 online resource (296 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aRomania Judaica : Studien zur jüdischen Kultur in den romanischen Ländern ,x1435-098X ;v40 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDer Band vereinigt die Kongressakten des gleichnamigen Kongresses, der im Mai 1998 in Münster stattfand. Die Schwerpunkte des Bandes bilden das politische Denken des französischen und italienischen Judentums einerseits und der Konflikt zwischen laizistischer und religiöser Orientierung im Staate Israel andererseits. Ausführlich erörtert wird sowohl der Wandel im Selbstverständnis des Diasporajudentums als auch die historische und aktuelle Deutung des Zionismus. Im Mittelpunkt steht dabei die Frage, ob Gerschom Scholems Hoffnung, dass aus der Entscheidung für Staatlichkeit und Geschichtlichkeit eine Erneuerung des Judentums folgen werde, für die Zukunft Gültigkeit bewahrt.  aThis volume contains the proceedings of the eponymous conference held in Münster in May 1998. Central concerns are a) Jewish political thinking in France and Italy, and b) the conflict between a laicist and a religious orientation in the state of Israel. There is detailed discussion both of the change in Jewish identity among diaspora Jews and of present-day and historical interpretations of the meaning of Zionism. Of crucial significance here is the question whether Gershom Scholem's hope that the decision in favour of statehood and historical awareness would lead to a revitalization of Judaism will retain its validity for the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aJudaism and politicsvCongresses. 0aJudaism and politicszFrancevCongresses. 0aJudaism and politicszIsraelvCongresses. 0aJudaism and politicszItalyvCongresses. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAzria, Régine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouretz, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrumlik, Micha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavarocchi Arbib, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFubini, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuetta, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalévy, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKilcher, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKriegel, Maurice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeir, Ephraim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiething, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiething, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPhilippe, Béatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaphael, Freddy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaz-Krakotzkin, Amnon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRother, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb